Date of Birth: November 1, 1800<br/>
Birthplace: Acton, Massachusetts, USA<br/>
Ordained apostle: April 25, 1835<br/>
Excommunicated:  March 17, 1839<br/>
Death: January 1866<br/>
<br/>
Born Nov. 1, 1800, at Acton, Middlesex Co., Massachusetts, to James Marsh and Molly Law.
Ordained apostle April 25, 1835, under the hands of Oliver Cowdery, David Whitmer, and Martin Harris, at Kirtland, Ohio, at age 35;
sustained as president of the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles May 2, 1835;
excommunicated March 17, 1839; rebaptized July 16, 1857; died January 1866, at Ogden, Weber Co., Utah, at age 66.
